How to style your airport look for a casual suit outfit | Traveling in a suit can be a challenge for many, but if you choose the right fit and fabrics, it won’t do any bad.
I chose my favourite linen stripes shirt, it keeps me cool and provides me room for easy movement. This time I went with a stretch denim as it doesn’t crease a lot compared to a dress pant. I chose Tassle loafers so that it becomes easy to take it off especially during security checks and I also remove my shoes when I sit in the plane, to complete the look I coped it with peach linen jacket with half lining and no shoulder pads. The jacket was easy to carry, lightweight and helped me keeping warm whenever it was cold at the airport.
